Package ca.umontreal.iro.ift2255.equipe13

Class ServiceManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.umontreal.iro.ift2255.equipe13.ServiceManager
  • public class ServiceManager
extends java.lang.Object
    ServiceManager is a class that contains a list of services given at GYM, a hash map of professionals to their services, and methods to create, fetch, or delete services

      • createService

        public boolean createService​(Professional offeredBy,
                             java.lang.String name,
                             java.lang.String beginningDate,
                             java.lang.String endDate,
                             java.lang.String serviceHour,
                             int capacity,
                             int cost,
                             java.lang.String comments,
                             java.lang.String[] recurrence)
        Tries to create a new service, and if successful, adds it to the services list.
        Parameters:
        offeredBy - a Professional.
        name - a String in format "Jon Doe".
        beginningDate - the String of a valid date in format "dd-mm-yyyy".
        endDate - the String of a valid date in format "dd-mm-yyyy".
        serviceHour - the String of a valid time in format "hh-mm".
        capacity - the capacity of the service, must be between 1 and 30.
        cost - the cost of the service, must be between 0 and 100.
        comments - comments, maximum 100 characters.
        recurrence - an array of strings representing the day of the week : "MONDAY" ...
        Returns:
        True if the service has been successfully created, or False if at least one of the parameters is invalid.
